<!--Pirate Quest Hub-->	
	<event name="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB" unique="true">
		<text>The nearby space station has been converted into a pirate hub. You can see a decent amount of pirates coming and going from the station, and the lack of proper security suggests that the pirates here trust each other to remain civil. You ponder what kind of pirate would be trusting of another pirate, but you shouldn't be denied entry if you wished to enter.</text>
		<choice>
			<text>Enter the hub.</text>
			<event load="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_ENTER"/>
		</choice>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Attack the pirates while they're off guard!</text>
			<event load="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_ATTACK"/>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Ignore the hub.</text>
			<event>
				<text>Even if you could enter, Federation officers aren't popular around pirate gangs. Who knows whether the pirates will turn hostile against you? Best not to poke your nose in pirates' businesses that probably don't affect the Federation.</text>
				<choice>
					<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
					<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
				<choice>
					<text>Do nothing.</text>
					<event/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
	</event>

	<event name="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_ENTER">
		<loadEventList first="true" default="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_ENTER_SUCCESS">
			<event name="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_ENTER_FAIL" req="rep_pirate" lvl="-999" max_lvl="-2"/>
		</loadEventList>
	</event>

	<event name="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_ENTER_FAIL">
		<text>Despite having been hostile towards the pirates on numerous occasions, you decide to enter anyways. The main hall falls silent as you make your entry, with a few pirates glaring in your direction. You sense that your presence here isn't welcomed at all and you hasten to leave, but not before a gang of rowdy pirates chase you back on foot!</text>
		<boarders min="3" max="4" class="LIST_CREW_PIRATE_RANDOM"/>
	</event>

	<event name="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_ENTER_SUCCESS">
		<text>Upon entry, it becomes clear that this is some sort of leisure place for pirates seeking a rest from their "work". Pirates from various factions are hanging out at the bar and playing some alien-version of pool. Most of the leisure activities don't interest you, but a further exploration of the station leads you to find various pirates requesting for services. Ironically, one of the pirates requesting a service is a Syndicate mercenary.</text>
		<choice req="rep_slaver" lvl="-999" max_lvl="-2" hidden="true">
			<text>You doubt that the slaver will entertain you.</text>
			<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
		</choice>
		<choice req="rep_slaver" lvl="-1" blue="false">
			<text>Approach the slaver.</text>
			<event load="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_SLAVER"/>
		</choice>
		<choice req="rep_mercenary" lvl="-999" max_lvl="-2" hidden="true">
			<text>You doubt that the mercenary will entertain you.</text>
			<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
		</choice>
		<choice req="rep_mercenary" lvl="-1" blue="false">
			<text>Approach the mercenary.</text>
			<event load="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_MERCENARY"/>
		</choice>
		<choice req="rep_smuggler" lvl="-999" max_lvl="-2" hidden="true">
			<text>You doubt that the smuggler will entertain you.</text>
			<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
		</choice>
		<choice req="rep_smuggler" lvl="-1" blue="false">
			<text>Approach the smuggler.</text>
			<event load="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_SMUGGLER"/>
		</choice>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>There's nothing here for us, let's leave.</text>
			<event/>
		</choice>
	</event>

	<eventList name="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_ATTACK">
		<event>
			<text>You blast the empty ships with ease while the pirates are inside the hub. However, before you can salvage most of the wreck, your sensors indicate a larger fleet of pirates approaching. You hasten to leave with your current haul before the fleet can give chase.</text>
			<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="REPUTATION_DECREASE_PIRATES"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
		<event>
			<text>You swoop in and take out most of the pirates' ships before they even realise they're under attack. Without any other means of self-defense, they reluctantly surrender. You promise to leave them alone after salvaging a few of their ships that you destroyed.</text>
			<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="REPUTATION_DECREASE_PIRATES"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
		<event>
			<text>While the hub might lack proper protection, it is still a meeting point for pirates who aren't afraid to fight back. A pirate ship that was about to dock notices your weapons coming online and moves in to stop you. The fight brings you out of range of the hub, but your aggression wouldn't have gone unnoticed either.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_PIRATE_ALL" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="REPUTATION_DECREASE_PIRATES_COMBAT"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
		<event>
			<text>While the hub might lack proper protection, it is still a meeting point for pirates who aren't afraid to fight back. A group of pirates who were resting in their ships spot you and chase you off. The fight brings you out of range of the hub, but you're still being targeted by multiple pirates, who continue to provide fire support against you in the background while you engage their leader.</text>
			<ship load="PIP_SHIP_PIRATE_HUB_MANY" hostile="true"/>
			<environment target="player" type="PDS"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="REPUTATION_DECREASE_PIRATES_COMBAT"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</eventList>


	<eventList name="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_SLAVER">
		<event>
			<text>The slaver seems surprised to be approached by a Federation renegade, but quickly gets to the point. "Those Coalition bastards have been messing up my crew on countless occasions. When I heard that there were a few Coalition ships nearby, I realised that it'd be a great opportunity to get some revenge. I would've gone after them myself, but I'm still too low on trained crew to risk confrontation, so I'm looking for people willing to go after their squad. Take any one of them out in any way you like and I'll give you one of my slaves for free."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Go after a standard Coalition ship.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Good, good. Just give me a call once you've dealt with them."</text>
					<quest event="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_SLAVER_COALITION"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Go after an elite Coalition ship.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Daring today, are we? I'll be sure to have a better slave awaiting you if you can take down this bad boy."</text>
					<quest event="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_SLAVER_COALITION_ELITE"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Decline the offer.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Ugh, fine, then stop wasting my time. Let me find someone who'll actually help me out."</text>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</eventList>

	<eventList name="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_MERCENARY">
		<event>
			<text>The mercenary takes a long sip from his beer and a long drag from his cigarette before addressing you. "If you're wonderin' why I'm not performing services for the slavers and smugglers over there, it's because I don't feel like pickin' a fight this week. I'd much rather cause some chaos without the risk of fightin' another angry ship, you know? What I want you to do is to help me take out some targets that my other clients hired me to take down. Knowin' you're a Fed, you'll probably like going after some Rebels, and fortunately I've got 2 of them on my current tab."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Go after a standard Rebel ship.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Alright, here's the coordinates of the Rebel ship. Call me once you've eliminated them and I'll mess around with the fleet..."</text>
					<quest event="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_MERCENARY_REBEL"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Go after an elite Rebel ship.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Alright, here's the coordinates of the Rebel ship. I know this is a tougher one, so call me once you've eliminated them and I'll give the fleet a giant headache..."</text>
					<quest event="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_MERCENARY_REBEL_ELITE"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Decline the offer.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Fine by me. If you change your mind I'll be here." Unfortunately for him, you don't have time to wait here as the Rebel fleet is on the move.</text>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</eventList>
	
	<eventList name="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_SMUGGLER">
		<event>
			<text>The smuggler looks up from his clipboard when you approach, squinting through his thick glasses to take a look at you. You're not sure what he thinks of you, but he presents his offer all the same. "I've just received a large shipment of goods to transfer to nearby Argeonn stations. Problem is, my boys pissed off the local police by blowing one of their stations up, so I've been flagged as a wanted fugitive. It's too risky for me to make the delivery myself, so I'm forced to turn to people like you for help. Complete the delivery and the people at the station will pay you well, though I must warn you that they may be blocked off by a hostile enforcer."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Deliver goods to a small outpost for a decent reward and low risk.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The smuggler signals for his team to pass you some crates. "No need to contact me for a reward, the outpost will know the delivery came from me. Good luck with the delivery, and try not to get yourself blown up."</text>
					<quest event="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_SMUGGLER_DELIVERY"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		    <choice hidden="true">   
				<text>Deliver goods to a big outpost for a larger reward but higher risk.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The smuggler signals for his team to go with you and load your ship with the crates in the docking area. "No need to contact me for a reward, the outpost will know the delivery came from me. Good luck with the delivery, and try not to get yourself blown up."</text>
					<quest event="PIP_QUEST_PIRATE_HUB_SMUGGLER_DELIVERY_HARD"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Decline the offer.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The smuggler snorts and goes back to reading his clipboard. After waiting for a minute in awkward silence, you figure that's your cue to leave.</text>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</eventList>
	
