	<event name="PIP_DISTRESS_PIRATE_OVERWORK" unique="true">
		<distressBeacon/>
		<text>The source of the distress beacon is a pirate ship nearby. Their weapons are offline, but you detect their core systems still running. The pirates make no move to hail you.</text>
		<ship load="SHIP_PIRATE_ALL" hostile="false"/>
		<choice>
			<text>Hail the pirates.</text>
			<event>
				<text>No one picks up your hails, but you find that the pirates are talking on an open channel. You tune in and listen to what the supposed captain of the ship is saying. "Aye, Mikey, this pirate business is worse than we expected! We were sold on stories of comfort through stealing and not working for your own money, but this is even more STRESSFUL! I never should have left my job man. Remember that time when we had union benefits? I sure do..."</text>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Keep listening, though it might take a while.</text>
					<event>
						<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
						<text>The pirate goes on to talk about his old job and life as a Union factory worker, about the bad working conditions, the stress of low income and the fear of being trapped in an eternal nine-to-five job. Then he talks about the time when he ditched that life to become a pirate, hoping it would free him from the rat race, only to find himself being overworked by taking on jobs for all three big pirate factions and having the additional stress of being shot at and chased down by the law enforcement. You're about to leave but he finally finishes his story. "And yeah, I guess we're here now. But what can I do now? I need some advice, dammit. Has anyone responded to our distress signal yet?"</text>
						<choice hidden="true">
							<text>Pitch in and offer to help.</text>
							<event>
								<text>"What? Aren't you one of those Federation officers? Not sure why you aren't shooting yet, but I'll take it. I don't know how long you've been listening for, but I'm assuming you know the predicament I'm in. Could you give some advice?"</text>
								<choice hidden="true">
									<text>Sounds like you need to take a vacation.</text>
									<event>
										<text>"Huh, I've never actually thought about that. I completely forgot that my hours are loose with the pirate factions. You know what? I think I will take a vacation, starting right now. But before I go and party at Sky Drifter Casino, have these random crates that are cluttering up my ship, as thanks for your great advice. I'm sure there's something useful in there for ya."</text>
										<choice hidden="true">
											<text>Open the first crate.</text>
											<event load="PIP_DISTRESS_PIRATE_OVERWORK_CRATE_1"/>
										</choice>
									</event>
								</choice>
								<choice hidden="true">
									<text>Perhaps you could drop one of your pirate jobs?</text>
									<event>
										<text>"Hm, that's actually a decent idea. Then I might finally experience a better working life! But which one should I drop?"</text>
										<choice hidden="true">
											<text>If you drop slavery then your slaves can also experience their own freedom.</text>
											<event>
												<text>"I suppose that's true. Ignoring the fact that I am still a mercenary and a smuggler, I feel like my moral standing has improved a little. Thank you, strange Federation ship. I will drop these fellas off at the next station, but I know one that seems to be eager to work aboard a vessel like yours."</text>
												<crewMember amount="1" class="LIST_SLAVES_GENERIC"/>
												<autoReward level="LOW">scrap_only</autoReward>
												<choice hidden="true">
													<text>Continue...</text>
													<event load="REPUTATION_UPDATE_PIRATES_FREE"/>
												</choice>
											</event>
										</choice>
										<choice hidden="true">
											<text>You won't have to be an errand-runner if you stop being a mercenary.</text>
											<event>
												<text>"That's a pretty good point. I've gotten some weird job requests before and I think I'm ready to leave those days behind. Thank you, strange Federation ship. As I am no longer in need of my mercenary equipment, help yourself to some of my equipment and a map of the sector."</text>
												<augment name="DISTRACTION_BUOY"/>
												<reveal_map/>
												<choice hidden="true">
													<text>Continue...</text>
													<event load="REPUTATION_UPDATE_PIRATES_FREE"/>
												</choice>
											</event>
										</choice>
										<choice hidden="true">
											<text>Ending your smuggling days will free up a lot of your ship space to do other stuff.</text>
											<event>
												<text>"Now that you mention it, I never really realised how crammed it was in here... Maybe I can buy myself some of those slot machines from Sky Drifter Casino to play in my free time in place of those smuggling crates. Thank you, strange Federation ship. Before I sell these items to fund the purchase of a slot machine, have one of them as thanks."</text>
												<autoReward level="LOW">item</autoReward>
												<choice hidden="true">
													<text>Continue...</text>
													<event load="REPUTATION_UPDATE_PIRATES_FREE"/>
												</choice>
											</event>
										</choice>
									</event>
								</choice>
								<choice hidden="true">
									<text>Go back to working in the factory, it's safer there.</text>
									<event>
										<text>The pirate stares wide-eyed at you for a few seconds before breaking into a maniacal laughter. "HAHAHAHA. Have you not been listening to my story this whole time? I became to be a pirate to escape that hellhole, and I'd rather die doing something epic than go back to being a slave to the Union! You have been most useless to me, but at least you've given me motivation to do my current job. My way of saying thank you is to steal all your stuff!"</text>
										<ship hostile="true"/>
										<choice hidden="true">
											<text>Continue...</text>
											<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
										</choice>
									</event>
								</choice>
								<choice hidden="true">
									<text>You're beyond help.</text>
									<event>
										<text>The pirate goes from a state of self-pity to anger the moment you finish your sentence. "Oh piss off, Federation! That is NOT what I meant by advice. If you aren't going to be useful, I'll just kill you and wait for the next ship to arrive and give me actual advice..."</text>
										<ship hostile="true"/>
										<choice hidden="true">
											<text>Continue...</text>
											<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
										</choice>
									</event>
								</choice>
							</event>
						</choice>
					</event>
				</choice>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>This isn't going anywhere useful, let's leave.</text>
					<event/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<text>Attack them!</text>
			<event>
				<text>Who knows if the distress beacon was a trap to lure unsuspecting civilians in? You'll be indirectly saving the lives of those who would have fallen victim to this trap. Assuming it was one, that is.</text>
